newsitem.title: EGYPT: Egypt overnight, one-week rates narrow.
newsitem.headline: Egypt overnight, one-week rates narrow.

text.p: Overnight interbank rates on the Egyptian pound narrowed on Tuesday in a liquid private sector market to between 10-1/8 and 10-1/4 percent from Monday's range of 10-1/8 and 10-1/2 percent, bankers said.
One-week rates narrowed to between 10-1/4 and 10-3/8 percent from 10-1/8 and 10-1/2 percent on Monday. Some bankers said they traded at rates as low as 10 percent.
The bankers said the central bank's repo deal worth 500 million pounds had injected liquidity in the market.
State-owned banks maintained their minimum overnight lending rate at 10-1/2 percent.
